wiki.content: The “Satanic” demo was the very first recorded session of VON, which was never released until now by VON. The Satanic session was recorded in early 1990 in San Francisco CA USA at the Union St. Studio. The songs as well as others that have not been released were played in many different places including garages, houses, studios, even outdoors through the years of (late 1988 - early 1990). Satanic Demo tracks include: 1) Venien *a song named after the bass player of the same name as well as the same song on the Satanic Blood Demo but mistyped Veinen on the cassette insert 2) Devil Pig (re-worked/re-recorded for the Satanic Blood Demo) 3) Veadtuck (re-worked/re-recorded for the Satanic Blood Demo) 4) Satanic (“working title”, later re-worked/re-recorded/re-named “Satanic Blood” for the Satanic Blood Demo) 5) Released (“working title” later re-worked/re-recorded/re-named “Release” for the Blood Angel Demo) 6) Lamb (re-worked/re-recorded for the Satanic Blood Demo) 7) Evisc (re-worked/re-recorded for the Blood Angel Demo) 8) Dissection (“working title” later renamed “Dissection InHuman” off and unreleased video of VON Live at the Stone in 1991 VHS) *special note: The Von Satanic Demo recordings are NOT on any other known bootleg re-recordings in current circulation, however some of the re-worked/re-recorded Satanic Blood and Blood Angel demo recordings are on bootlegs in the market today and are not endorsed by VON. There are only 3 know copies of the recordings made and those were for each of the founding band members: Von aka Goat, Vennt aka Snake, and Venien. more information on VON and VON Music visit the official site at www.vonmusicgroup.com Read more on Last.fm.
